1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,368
Welcome to Inner Child Play.

2
00:00:02,368 --> 00:00:08,269
This practice is an invitation to
reconnect with playfulness, imagination,

3
00:00:08,269 --> 00:00:08,916
and joy.

4
00:00:08,916 --> 00:00:11,842
You do not have to feel playful right
away.

5
00:00:11,842 --> 00:00:15,836
Sometimes playful parts are hidden behind
protectors.

6
00:00:15,836 --> 00:00:18,437
That is okay.

7
00:00:18,437 --> 00:00:21,920
Begin by settling your body.

8
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:24,660
Take a gentle breath in.

9
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:26,518
And let it out.

10
00:00:26,518 --> 00:00:32,184
Now notice any part of you that reacts to
the idea of play.

11
00:00:32,184 --> 00:00:35,435
Maybe a part feels excited.

12
00:00:35,435 --> 00:00:37,200
Maybe a part feels silly.

13
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,661
Maybe a part feels embarrassed.

14
00:00:39,661 --> 00:00:44,166
Maybe a part says, this is pointless.

15
00:00:44,166 --> 00:00:46,720
All of that is welcome.

16
00:00:46,720 --> 00:00:48,253
Now ask inside:

17
00:01:00,253 --> 00:01:00,253
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

18
00:01:00,253 --> 00:01:05,749
Is there a younger part of me that
remembers play, or wishes it had more

19
00:01:05,749 --> 00:01:06,755
room to play?

20
00:01:18,755 --> 00:01:18,755
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

21
00:01:18,755 --> 00:01:24,096
If a younger part appears, notice what
kind of play it is drawn toward.

22
00:01:24,096 --> 00:01:25,489
Maybe drawing.

23
00:01:25,489 --> 00:01:26,418
Dancing.

24
00:01:26,418 --> 00:01:27,068
Building.

25
00:01:27,068 --> 00:01:27,672
Running.

26
00:01:27,672 --> 00:01:28,229
Singing.

27
00:01:28,229 --> 00:01:28,972
Pretending.

28
00:01:28,972 --> 00:01:29,901
Exploring.

29
00:01:29,901 --> 00:01:30,690
Laughing.

30
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:32,176
Making something.

31
00:01:32,176 --> 00:01:33,476
Being messy.

32
00:01:33,476 --> 00:01:35,055
Being free.

33
00:01:35,055 --> 00:01:37,098
Ask this part:

34
00:01:49,098 --> 00:01:49,098
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

35
00:01:49,098 --> 00:01:53,092
What kind of play did you love, or wish
you had?

36
00:02:05,092 --> 00:02:05,092
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

37
00:02:05,092 --> 00:02:09,504
Now imagine creating a safe play space
for this part.

38
00:02:21,504 --> 00:02:21,504
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

39
00:02:21,504 --> 00:02:23,640
It might be a room full of art supplies.

40
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:24,847
A backyard.

41
00:02:24,847 --> 00:02:26,751
A playground.

42
00:02:26,751 --> 00:02:28,516
A beach.

43
00:02:28,516 --> 00:02:30,095
A pile of blankets.

44
00:02:30,095 --> 00:02:31,953
A music room.

45
00:02:31,953 --> 00:02:33,671
A magical world.

46
00:02:33,671 --> 00:02:36,782
Let it be whatever this part wants.

47
00:02:36,782 --> 00:02:37,850
Now ask:

48
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:49,850
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

49
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:53,658
What would you like to do here?

50
00:03:05,658 --> 00:03:05,658
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

51
00:03:05,658 --> 00:03:10,070
Imagine allowing this younger part to
play without criticism.

52
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:22,070
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

53
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:23,510
No one is judging.

54
00:03:23,510 --> 00:03:25,646
No one is rushing.

55
00:03:25,646 --> 00:03:28,293
No one is grading the outcome.

56
00:03:28,293 --> 00:03:33,123
If a critical or embarrassed part
appears, gently acknowledge it.

57
00:03:33,123 --> 00:03:34,609
You might say:

58
00:03:43,609 --> 00:03:43,609
<break time="3s" />

59
00:03:43,609 --> 00:03:45,374
I see you.

60
00:03:45,374 --> 00:03:49,879
You may be trying to protect me from
feeling foolish.

61
00:03:49,879 --> 00:03:56,600
You do not have to disappear, but maybe
you can give this younger part a little

62
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:57,031
room.

63
00:03:57,031 --> 00:04:00,328
Now return to the younger part.

64
00:04:00,328 --> 00:04:03,068
Let it have a few moments of play.

65
00:04:03,068 --> 00:04:08,269
Notice what happens in your body as this
part plays.

66
00:04:26,269 --> 00:04:26,269
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

67
00:04:26,269 --> 00:04:27,523
Maybe warmth.

68
00:04:27,523 --> 00:04:28,777
Maybe sadness.

69
00:04:28,777 --> 00:04:30,077
Maybe resistance.

70
00:04:30,077 --> 00:04:30,959
Maybe lightness.

71
00:04:30,959 --> 00:04:32,677
Maybe nothing obvious.

72
00:04:32,677 --> 00:04:34,813
Whatever happens is okay.

73
00:04:34,813 --> 00:04:37,414
Now ask the younger part:

74
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:49,414
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

75
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:52,293
What do you want me to remember about
play?

76
00:05:04,293 --> 00:05:04,293
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

77
00:05:04,293 --> 00:05:06,243
And:

78
00:05:06,243 --> 00:05:11,259
What is one small playful thing I could
let into my real life?

79
00:05:23,259 --> 00:05:23,259
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

80
00:05:23,259 --> 00:05:24,745
It could be tiny.

81
00:05:24,745 --> 00:05:25,952
A color.

82
00:05:25,952 --> 00:05:26,649
A song.

83
00:05:26,649 --> 00:05:27,438
A doodle.

84
00:05:27,438 --> 00:05:28,599
A silly movement.

85
00:05:28,599 --> 00:05:29,946
A few minutes outside.

86
00:05:29,946 --> 00:05:31,571
A playful object.

87
00:05:31,571 --> 00:05:34,729
A moment of imagination.

88
00:05:34,729 --> 00:05:38,584
Now thank this younger part for showing
you something.

89
00:05:38,584 --> 00:05:41,649
Let them know play does not have to be
earned.

90
00:05:50,649 --> 00:05:50,649
<break time="3s" />

91
00:05:50,649 --> 00:05:53,528
Joy does not have to be perfect.

92
00:05:53,528 --> 00:05:55,711
Take a slow breath in.

93
00:06:04,711 --> 00:06:04,711
<break time="3s" />

94
00:06:04,711 --> 00:06:06,058
And let it out.

95
00:06:06,058 --> 00:06:08,473
Return to the room around you.

96
00:06:17,473 --> 00:06:17,473
<break time="3s" />

97
00:06:17,473 --> 00:06:22,674
And consider one small way to let play
have a little space today.

98
00:06:22,674 --> 00:06:28,464
Your playful parts do not need to prove
their usefulness. Joy, imagination,

99
00:06:28,464 --> 00:06:33,942
wonder, and silliness are not
distractions from healing. Sometimes they

100
00:06:33,942 --> 00:06:38,324
are part of how healing finds its way
back into the body.

101
00:06:38,324 --> 00:06:42,086
------------------------------------------
------------------------------.

